<P>
   SCI-GIJOE-PHYSIQUE (Undated) _ Barbie has a male companion in
the land of the outlandish physique, and his name ain't Ken.
Instead, we must look to that old trooper, G.I. Joe, to see a match
for Barbie's cartoon anatomy, and to find a doll that may be as
insidious a role model for boys as Barbie is for girls. Some
researchers worry that Joe and other action-hero figures may
contribute to the use of muscle-building drugs among young
athletes, even as doctors and sports officials struggle to
emphasize that such drugs are not only risky, illegal and
unsporting, but in many cases actually worthless to performance. By
Natalie Angier.
</P>
<P>
   SCI-TIME-REVERSAL (Undated) _ Since a landmark experiment in
1964 by Dr. James Cronin and Dr. Val Fitch, physicists have known
that time reversal is not so neat in the microscopic world of
particles. They found indirect but convincing evidence that
sometimes a particle going backward in time fails to land on the
metaphorical diving board; in other words, time, they found, could
not be perfectly symmetrical. Experimenters have now achieved
direct confirmation of this unsettling inference. By Malcolm W.
Browne. (1820 words)
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Graphic has been sent to NYT graphics clients.)
</P>
<P>
   SCI-CANCER-TREATMENT (Undated) _ A novel form of cancer
treatment has neared the end of its preliminary trials with
promising results at the same time as new research has cast doubt
on its original rationale. The doubts, not yet resolved, may mean
that the treatment is less innocuous to normal cells than thought.
But it is also possible that the treatment may be applicable to a
much wider range of cancers than previously believed. The agent of
treatment is a genetically altered adenovirus, one of the viruses
that cause the common cold. By Nicholas Wade.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Graphic has been sent to NYT graphics clients.)
</P>
<P>
   SCI-BIRDS-MONOGAMY (Undated) _ In study after study, the idea
that females are naturally devoted to their one and only mates,
even as the males wander, has fallen to growing evidence that many
of the world's females are anything but monogamous. In spite of
these findings, many biologists held out hope that some females
might be faithful, particularly to exemplary, hard-working fathers,
as in the bird species known as the wattled jacana. But research
reported today in the Proceedings of the Royal Society shatters
that dream. Although the diminutive male jacanas do everything to
care for the eggs and young of their raucous, beefy females _ these
males are cuckolded. By Carol Kaesuk Yoon.
</P>
<P>
   SCI-SCHALLER-BIODIVERSITY (Undated) _ George Schaller, director
of science for the Wildlife Conservation Society, the group that
runs the Bronx Zoo, has studied animals in the wild for more than
45 years, from the birds of Colville River, Alaska, to the mountain
gorillas of Zaire and the giant pandas of China. He discussed
biodiversity and his current field work _ trying to gauge the
impact of an epidemic of bacterial hoof disease on the vast herds
of gazelles on the Central Asian steppe _ in a telephone interview
from a campsite near Choybalsan in eastern Mongolia. By John
O'Neil.
</P>
<P>
   SCI-AIDS-MINORITIES (Undated) _ Harlem AIDS Forum examines the
way minorities are finding alternative disease treatments. By David
France.
</P>
<P>
   SCI-TEETH-WHITENERS (Undated) _ A variety of new procedures and
products have become available for whitening darkened or discolored
teeth. But dental experts warn that some of them can not only
damage the teeth they are whitening but also can present general
health risks. By Holcolm B. Noble.
</P>
<P>
   SCI-CAUSE-OF-DEATH (Undated) _ The Doctor's World column: New
evidence of flawed death certificate information comes from
researchers at the federally financed Framingham Heart Study in
Massachusetts. The study, begun in 1948 and involving some 10,000
people, suggests that doctors overstate coronary artery disease as
a cause of death on death certificates, particularly among the
elderly. Few doctors are trained in listing cause of death, but
steps are being taken to teach them, including step-by-step
electronic certificate-filing programs. By Lawrence K. Altman.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Graphic has been sent to NYT graphics clients.)
</P>
<P>
   SCI-FITNESS-CHILD (Undated) _ Exercising with a young child in a
jogging stroller, bike seat or backpack has its advantages and
appeal, but safety experts offer a long list of cautions. By John
O'Neil.
</P>
