   on the Web.
</P>
<P>
   Other organizations that offer mature travelers some
people-to-people experiences include:
</P>
<P>
   &UR; _ The Friendship Force, &LR;  whose motto, ``A World of Friends is a
World of Peace,'' encourages its members to live with average
people in countries throughout the world, or to be a host to
foreign travelers to the United States. The cost of membership is
$12 a year. Call (404) 522-9490; or visit www./friendship-force.org
on the Web.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; _ Grand Circle Travel &LR;  incorporates people-to-people
opportunities into their programs on a regular basis. For example,
trips to Portugal, Spain, Australia and New Zealand include a
segment called ``A Taste of Village Life,'' in which travelers are
treated to a home-hosted lunch. Call (800) 248-3737 for a catalog.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; _The Bahamas Tourist office, &LR;  (242) 328-7810, can provide
information about its people-to-people program, which includes
visiting local homes for dinner or going to church with residents.
The program is free to travelers, but you must sign up for it
either before you leave home or upon arrival.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; _The Japanese National Tourist Organization &LR;  (JNTO) also offers
what it calls a ``Home Visit System.'' Information is available
from any JNTO office. In New York, (212) 757-5640.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; _ Seniors Abroad &LR;  is a special program just for mature
travelers that has been operating for 15 years under the guidance
of Evelyn Zivetz of San Diego. She organizes homestays for
travelers heading to Japan, New Zealand and Australia. For more
information, write to her at 12533 Pacato Circle North, San Diego,
Calif. 92128; e-mail, haev(AT)pacbell.net.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; _ Friends Overseas &LR;  costs $25, which will get you a list of
people in Scandinavian countries who are willing to spend time with
tourists. For information, send a No. 10 envelope with your address
and a first-class stamp to Friends Overseas, 68-04 Dartmouth St.,
Forest Hills, N.Y. 11375; (718) 544-5660. &QL; 
 &UR; ----- &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Readers are invited to submit questions and comments to Gene and
Adele Malott, c/o The New York Times Syndicate, 122 East 42nd St.,
14th Floor, New York, N.Y. 10168. Send the Malotts a postcard from
your trip with ideas, questions and information on the bargains you
find for seniors.
</P>
<P>
   Questions may also be sent to the Malotts by electronic mail.
The address is MatureTrav(at)aol.com. (For (AT) use the symbol on
your keyboard.)
</P>
<P>
   The Malotts are the publishers of THE MATURE TRAVELER: Travel
Bonanzas for 49ers-Plus, a newsletter for mature travelers.
