<HEADLINE>
LOVING THE LAP OF LUXURY 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By RICHARD P. CARPNTER  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   People do love their luxury. The Brown Palace Hotel in Denver
recently tracked the purchase of luxury items and services by its
guests, and here's what it found:
</P>
<P>
   --At Churchill, the hotel's cigar bar and restaurant, 23
customers last year spent up to $295 for a pre-Castro 1954 Dunhill
cigar.
</P>
<P>
   --Sales of Dom Perignon champagne, at $195 per bottle, increased
4 percent. Eighteen guests shelled out $300 for a bottle of
Roederer's Cristal Rose champagne, but only three went for Opus
One, at $260 a bottle. Sales of Johnny Walker Blue Label at $35 per
glass were up 16 percent.
</P>
<P>
   --Sales in the on-site flower shop increased 8.6 percent between
1996 and 1997. In the same time span, guest laundry revenue rose
4.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
   --And this year, one guest indulged her spouse with the hotel's
Ultimate Experience Package. The cost: a mere $4,500.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Travel Trivia: Which country owns the Galapagos Islands? (Answer
at end of column.)
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   In a name: A pub in Canterbury, England, serves a brew called
``Old Bishop Fingers.'' (With thanks and happy holidays to frequent
contributor Mike Schuster of Foxborough.)
</P>
<P>
   Quotable: When Al Calk of Brockton asked a New York City
waitress ``what section of the city are we in right now?,'' she
replied without hesitation, ``The non-smoking section.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Advice to go: Always show respect when visiting another country.
Not long ago, four British tourists were jailed after being
photographed displaying their buttocks in the ruins of an ancient
palace at Knossos on Crete.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   They're everywhere! If you think there are a lot of
motorscooters in Florence, Italy, you're right. There are a
quarter-million of them _ an average of two per family.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Honeymoon aloha: Hawaii is the most romantic honeymoon spot,
according to a survey by Modern Bride magazine. The runners-up, in
descending order, are Tahiti, Italy, France, Jamaica, St. Lucia,
Bermuda, Fiji, Greece, and Bali.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Did you guess it? Ecuador.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Send comments and questions to Travel Tidbits, Boston Globe,
Boston, MA 02107. Send e-mail to carpen(at)nws.globe.com)
</P>
</TEXT>
