<HEADLINE>
RAFT MAINE HAS A WINTER ANSWER: SNOWMOBILING 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By JERRY MORRIS  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   What do white-water rafters do in winter? Go snowmobiling. Six
members of the Raft Maine trade association have formed a winter
marketing group to promote snowmobile vacations. The companies of
Sled Maine offer resorts on the snowmobile trail system. Facilities
offer lodging, dining, and snowmobiling rentals. Some resorts
include hot tubs and saunas, entertainment, snowshoeing,
cross-country skiing, and ice fishing. For information, call Sled
Maine at 877-275-3363.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL; 
Alaska needs you!
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Alaska State Parks is looking for volunteers to serve as
campground hosts, ranger assistants, natural history interpreters,
and trail crew. Volunteers must be at least 18, and are generally
provided with housing and a small expense allowance. Transportation
to and from Alaska is not provided. For a catalog of positions and
descriptions, write to Volunteer Coordinator, Alaska State Parks,
3601 C St., Suite 1200, Anchorage, AK 99503; or call 907-269-8708,
fax 907-269-8907, or e-mailvolunteer(at)dnr.state.ak.us.
</P>
