<P>
   Everyone's talking about Harold Evans' epic work, ``The American
Century,'' a national best seller that captures the great events,
personalities and movements of the past 100 years.
</P>
<P>
   Now this engaging work is available to newspapers in short bites
of 100 words each. Use one a day in 1999, or compile them to form
weekly or monthly specials _ WITH ART!
</P>
<P>
   To celebrate the release of these excerpts, The New York Times
Syndicate is running a history trivia quiz based on the book. Every
day this week we are offering on the wire one question related to
the world of journalism. The first editor to fax back the correct
answer will win a copy of ``The American Century.''
</P>
<P>
   THE ANSWER TO YESTERDAY'S QUESTION: McClure's Magazine was the
publication in which Ida Tarbell exposed the coercion and spying
behind John Rockefeller's oil monopoly.
</P>
<P>
   Congratulations to PAUL TOOHER, Senior News Editor at the
Providence Journal. A copy of ``The American Century'' is in the
mail!
</P>
