<P>
   SANTA-WORLDWIDE &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ The American idea of Santa has taken hold all over the
world _ the roly-poly red-suited one has become a popular figure in
countries as far-flung as Brazil, the Philippines and Ghana. But
many countries have developed their own versions of Santa _ or
maintained other holiday figures _ that better fit their own
traditions. Here's a multinational seasonal sampler of traditions
from Italy, Mexico, Norway and more. By LIZ STEVENS. Story has
moved in ``l'' lifestyle category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ANDERSON-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ In a previous column, I said that I was learning to
wrestle by watching a video called ``Wrestling For Moms'' or
``Hugging With An Attitude.'' I thought that if I learned to
wrestle, I would have a remote chance of getting closer than arm's
length to at least one of my two sons. Well, after spending several
hours sitting in a hot tub laced with Epsom salts, I have come to
the conclusion that hugging is highly overrated. In the future, I
shall be content with that handshake of gratitude and affection
that they give me on the third Friday of the month. By MONICA
ANDERSON Story has moved in ``l'' lifestyle category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   TRIVIA-Q&AMP;A &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ How did Kenneth Starr come to be special prosecutor?
By ROGERS CADENHEAD. Story has moved in ``l'' lifestyle category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
