<P>
   NATIVITY-EXHIBITION &QL;
</P>
<P>
   DALLAS _ Nary a photograph nor sketch recorded the scene 2,000
years ago, yet each detail endures in collective memory: Mary and
Joseph and the shepherds, the smell of hay, the rustle of cattle,
the vision of baby Jesus. We know the scene because we have seen it
through the eyes of Rembrandt and Tintoretto, El Greco, Gauguin and
Sunday school coloring books. Now the Biblical Arts Center in
Dallas is featuring an exhibit called ``Nativity.'' By MATTHEW
BRADY. Story has moved in ``e'' arts/entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
