<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CORRECTIONS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR WEDNESDAY, DECEMBER 23
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Wednesday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-POLAND-AUSCHWITZ-NYT (moved on Saturday, Dec. 19)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Saturday, Dec. 19,
about a dispute between Jews and Catholics over crosses outside the
Auschwitz death camp misspelled the surname of Poland's Prime
Minister. He is Jerzy Buzek, not Burek. The article also misspelled
the surname of a historian who commented on the dispute. He is
Jerzy Jedlicki, not Ledlicki.
</P>
<P>
   BC-MIDEAST-HILLARY-NYT (moved on Sunday, Dec. 13)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, Dec. 13,
about Hillary Rodham Clinton's visit to Israel with President
Clinton misidentified the site where Yitzhak Rabin, the former
Israeli Prime Minister, is buried and where the Clintons attended a
memorial gathering. It is on Mount Herzl, not the Mount of Olives.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-12-22-98 2150EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
